main event: An unidentified object was observed via radar making passes at a high altitude and speed over the Pacific.
interesting points: The sighting was registered on 31 January 1963 at a location of 20°N 170°W., The object was recorded at an altitude of 20,000 feet and a speed of 370 knots., Another report indicated an object making passes at 24,000 feet with a speed of 360 knots., The object did not use any lights and appeared to be utilizing radar., The report was transmitted to various military and intelligence agencies including the CIA and DIA.
sighted object: an unidentified object observed via radar
